      "content": "I see. So you're suggesting that the \"desirable character\" is tied to keeping the community structure the same. In real estate terms, isn't that often just a way of saying that when a neighborhood transitions from a more homogenous, established demographic to a more diverse one, it's viewed as a loss of value? Is there any data suggesting these demographic shifts actually lead to decline, or is that more of an assumption?",
