      "content": "The perception of value is heavily tied to the established social fabric, and rapid change often signals a loss of that familiar character. While some might argue otherwise, historical trends in high-end real estate often show that sudden, drastic shifts in composition can introduce uncertainty that deters the highest-tier buyers. The assumption is based on the pattern that stability, not flux, is what preserves premium property values.",
